Need for Speed: The Run is running across America.
Review
Originally, careless driving, due to a series of completely unnecessary laidake errors, turns into a routine morning journey on the shell.
The ambition has been achieved to a great extent, but it is nothing valid when no one obviously wanted to do anything extra.
The new episode with the subtitle The Run raised high expectations before the release.
He promised that the yearly racing series Need for Speed again will move a bit in a new direction and from the playable shows it appeared as a game that would not have to be just in the genre of action racing.
We were also curious about how the inserted passages will fall, in which the main hero will go out of the car and take on his own.
As in the NFS series it is a habit, many results are a little different than we expected.
These are potentially decent arcade races, but the whole draws down a few unnecessary mistakes that appear in the series more than a few years ago.
So it’s actually not a mistake, but rather a manifestation of some uncomprehensible leness of developers.
The adventure begins very well.
You are listed in the story whose protagonist Jack has certain personal problems and as a solution it is offered to participate in an illegal race across America.
You will sit behind the wheel on the west coast of San Francisco and your task is to arrive first to New York.
The idea brings with it several interesting elements.
The route is divided into ten stages, and then more than fifty races.
It follows that each race goes on a different track and the given stages are placed in different, sufficiently different and interesting environments.
You don’t feel like the game is always the same.
Some of the environments are also very nice to look, although the technical level of graphics corresponds to the previous parts of the series.
This is nothing worldwide.
But riding across the desert, autumn landscape or high in snowed mountains is visually very pleasant.
In addition, the races are from time to time sprinkled with some unusual element.
In the desert, for example, you get into a sand storm, which significantly decreases the visibility.
On the contrary, in the mountains again you need to be careful so that you are not drowned by the lavina.
In addition, the different races are well performed.
There are only a few types, but it is enough.
For a moment, you try to overcome the desired number of opponents (in essence a classic race), then you get time (a classic match with the stickers) and then you are waiting for a duel with a single opponent.
It is also a time to time for the police to get involved, which further discomforts your efforts.
The new is the passages outside the car.
It’s rather just such an interactive animation, when Jack mostly escapes from someone and you have to help him in doing so that in the right moments you print the right buttons.
Nothing complicated.
It will be surprising, however, that these passages are much less in the game than you would expect (especially even just three).
As a result, it is in favour of the thing, because this element has no chance to become annoying, and in the context of the above, it is so ranked to the elements that spread the game.
The driving model goes in the footsteps of the previous parts.
This means that it is definitely no longer known, but it cannot be said that it would be a negative.
If you’re looking for a realistic simulation, you’ll have to look elsewhere.
But more action-conscious racing here’s driving model fits still quite well, although we could find better at the competition.
Until then everything is perfectly okay.
Problems begin to appear after a while.
Unlike the motorcycle model, the motorcycle model is no longer good.
From the game of this type we don’t expect it to count complex deformations and collisions, but when practically before any collision into any object you don’t have the smallest idea how your car will beined, then probably isn’t all okay.
Typically, when you get closely ahead or pass the cars in normal traffic, you sometimes only slightly fold each other, but other times in a almost identical situation your car will end in wild piruets.
Or even directly.
Thanks to the restart system, it doesn’t really bother you, but it will break you reliably.
Restartes are resolved in such a way that if you break down or go far out of the track, the game will throw you back to the last catch point on the track.
There are only five rebounds available in each race.
When you get out of them, you have to start the race again from the beginning.
It is, therefore, rather such a help for the case that something does not succeed, than that you could expressly rely on them.
But sometimes even restarts will not help, they will be solved by the need to learn the given part of the race to remember.
The big disadvantage of the game is that the same things often happen in the same places.
Some curtains, for example, need to go in a specific way, otherwise you won’t get into them.
Other times you will meet on a given place “civil” cars always in the same configuration whether you arrive there first, fifth, five seconds earlier or a minute later.
It is especially angry in situations where you see the opponent between the two contrary cars before you easily pass, while when you get there, the cars are already in such a position that you have to circumvent them or brake them.
It doesn’t matter when you get to them, because it’s “calculated” so that the situation always occurs right before your nose.
The competitors have another advantage.
Thro the time of playing you will encounter several places where you, again regardless of the time, will always be ahead of the same opponent in the same place.
Most of it dirty at the end of the game on a long bridge, where you go in the opposite direction.
The opponent must come there before you obviously for any price.
When it goes ahead of you, it makes you worse the overview of the contrary cars, so you start there about a couple of times.
You can understand the intention to make the game more stressful and adrenaline, but the performance is so obvious that it will reliably quickly disappoint you.
And it’s a shame, because despite the simple driving model, playing is fun and places even so actionful that sometimes you literally don’t watch where it flies.
And it’s essentially no matter whether it’s worth a concept with fifty unique trails, ranging the races so that tired doesn’t have a chance, or anything else.
An unusual idea is the exchange of cars during races.
You have to pay attention to the petrol pumps on the road, because there you can change the car, although in the vast majority of cases you will get enough with what you have.
The cars are divided into three categories.
Athletes are suitable for urban areas, strong American buses on straight highways and exotic super sports for technical riding, for example, on clocked mountain roads.
With the main story mode goes hand in hand and the challenge mode, which is the races in the individual locations you know from the story.
Here you get not only medals, but also experience points into your profile, which is common for challenges and the story.
To get a higher driver level, various items are opened: starting with cars and ending with backgrounds for the profile.
It is also connected to the Autolog online feature, which, among other things, compares your achieved results with other players and obtains additional community features.
One of the other difficult to understand is the situation from the last race in the story.
With your car you get to the tunnel of the metro (budiž), where you marry it in the dark on the rails (budiž).
