The technical side of the game is nothing extra, but at least the overall visual impression is in most cases very pleasant and in a few cases even great.
It freezes so that in some more exhausted moments the recording decreases, and in some cases quite tragically.
This applies, however, primarily to the buracks with a greater number of participants, when the smooth drawing is no longer valid.
The sound page is fine and the soundtrack is a matter of taste.
In an attempt to enjoy the wider scale of a younger audience, a soundtrack from the category "every dog is different" was created, but it can be assumed that because of the listening to music, the game will not be purchased.
Need for Speed: The Run is a great deal.
If the game avoided completely unnecessary errors, then we’t be afraid to say that The Run is the best piece of NFS in the past few years.
