In the 1960s, humans and computers from IBM helped NASA control flights to space - on Mercury, Saturn and in 1969 the famous flight of man to the moon.
Meanwhile, in 1964, IBM developed the first family of computers - the IBM System/360 series.
The classic “peach” that established the computer standard of that time, called IBM 5150, came on the market in 1981.
Twenty years later, IBM sold the computer production to the Chinese company Lenovo, on the contrary, it bought the consultancy part of the company PricewaterhouseCoopers and began to dedicate itself fully to high added value consultancy and services.
