In Michoacán, they analyze the possibility of counting "voice by voice"
According to the data published by the PREP, the difference between the first and second places in the governor's elections is less than 27 percent.
The possibility of counting "voice by vote" appeared in this year's elections in Michoacán, where according to the data published by the Program for preliminary election results (PREP) the difference between the first and second place in the governor's elections is less than 27 per cent, and this has not yet been counted by the votes of 879 of the total 6074 electoral districts.
In this context, the Chairman of the General Council of the Electoral Institute in Michoacán (IEM), María de los Ángeles Llanderal Zaragoza, reminded that a few days ago, 9 November, the Electoral Authority approved a series of measures to harmonize local standards with the federal election reform.
As it will be recalled, Michoacán has not officially confirmed his political constitution or his State Electoral Code or the Law on Electoral Justice. The State Congress has approved the reforms shortly before the legal deadline for their entry into force had to pass in this election period and Governor Leonel Godoy Rangel has forgotten their publication within the specified deadline in the Law of the Official State Journal with the fact that he had some objection against them.
On 9 November, the Supreme State Court (SCJN) resolved the constitutional dispute initiated by the local legislative power and declared the head of state’s voice in the matter of constitutional reforms “invalid and illegal” because he has the right “neither to approve nor veto them”.
On the question of the possibility of counting "voice by voice" María de los Ángeles Llanderal replied that thanks to the approval of the relevant measures by the General Council of the IEM will be possible that partial and total counting is carried out by the local electoral authority.
In this way, the partial counting of votes, one or more voting packages, will be possible under the following conditions: voting results disagree; there is no registration of voting and calculation in the corresponding box or it is not available by the Chairman; or if there have been errors and obvious violations of the voting results.
In addition, a total recounting of votes in all elections will be possible if there is indication that the difference between the potential winner of the elections and the candidate in the second place is less or equal to one percentage point; whenever at the beginning of the session appears an explicit request from the representative of the party and/or the coalition that proposed the candidate in the second place.
The total recounting of votes will also be possible when, after a proper counting, the difference between the likely winner and the candidate in the second place is equal or less than one percentage point and also whenever there is an explicit request from a political party whose candidate ended in the second place.
It should be noted that in such a situation there are elections in Morelia, where according to the PREP the difference between the first and second places is less than 0.16%, although 129 of the total 923 electoral districts have not yet been counted.
